des:
Control Airam SmartHome devices with Airam SmartHome Skill. There is no need to adjust your devices manually – just ask Alexa on your smartphone or Amazon Echo device to do it for you. 
Follow these few simple steps to connect your Airam Smarthome account with Amazon Alexa App, then you can start to enjoy the full voice control with our smart devices. 

1). Prepare “Airam SmartHome” devices available in hand; 
(2). Download our "Airam SmartHome" app from Google Play or iOS App Store
(3). Register your account in our "Airam SmartHome" app, create username and password;
(4). Configure your devices in “Airam SmartHome" app and change appropriate names for your devices, which will be used also in Amazon Alexa app;
(5). Download “Amazon Alexa" app from Google Play, iOS App Store or Amazon Appstore;
(6). Search "Airam SmartHome" skill from the "Amazon Alexa" app skills category;
(7). Click “ENABLE TO USE” skill of "Airam SmartHome", and you'll be navigated to Airam SmartHome login page;
(8). Open "Airam SmartHome" App, click More Service, choose "Alexa". Link with Verification Code, copy the Code, put code into the login page；
(9). Now all setup is finished. You can try to give voice command to your home device as below. 

“Alexa, turn on kitchen light ” 
“Alexa, turn off kitchen light ”
“Alexa, dim living room light”
“Alexa, set bedroom light to Red”
